<dl>
<dt><font size="-1">04/04/2011</font></dt>
<dt><a href="episodes/episode_64.mp3"><font size="+2">Episode 64: Rich Missed the Train!</font></a></dt>
<font size="+1">
<dd>
We don't need no stinkin Rich!
Chris and Earl discuss the concept of railroading in games.
True to our style of sandbox gaming, our discussion jumps the rails,
but always comes back on topic.
Mostly.
Hang around after the disclaimer for an extended discussion.
</dd>
<br>
<dt>Cast:
<a class="SUBMENU" href="/about.php#chris">Chris</a>
<a class="SUBMENU" href="/about.php#earl"> and Earl</a>
</dt>
  <dd><img src="miniblob.gif"></dd>
<br>
<dd><dt>Quicklinker:</dt>
  <dd><a href="http://www.originsgamefair.com">Origins</a></dd>
</dd></font>
<dt><font size="-1">runtime: ~105 minutes</font></dt>
</dl><dl>
<dt><font size="-1">03/14/2011</font></dt>
<dt><a href="episodes/episode_63.mp3"><font size="+2">Episode 63: Putting the Magic back in Magic</font></a></dt>
<font size="+1">
<dd>
Mr Ed Healy joins us again for a discussion on how RPG magic is being taken for granted, 
treated as a player right, and has become totally mundane.
We provide some suggestions how to make magic fantastic and how to make it a source
of surprise and story tension once again.
All of this without CHEATING the players.
Well, maybe there's a little cheating.
</dd>
<br>
<dt>Cast:
<a class="SUBMENU" href="/about.php#rich">Rich</a>
<a class="SUBMENU" href="/about.php#chris">, Chris</a>
